Introduction to Neural Networks covers Multi-Layered Perceptron, extending from one-layered perceptron to solve multi-class classification, regression, and non-linear separable classes. Frank Rosenblatt's 1957 "Mark-1" hardware, the Perceptron, was an early neural network for recognizing geometric shapes. It had 400 inputs and one output, using weights as potentiometers. The Perceptron is a binary classifier, trained by adjusting weights to minimize errors. A Python algorithm demonstrates training using gradient descent.
